# Apache Kafka Introduction - Complete Project Documentation

## Project Overview

This is a personal training project for learning Apache Kafka fundamentals and real-world producer-consumer patterns. The project demonstrates how to build event-driven systems using Kafka with a practical example: **Order Event Processing System**.

The project is based on the learning materials from the "Kafka Zero to Hero" repository by Iam Veeramalla (https://github.com/iam-veeramalla/kafka-zero-to-hero). It provides hands-on examples of producing and consuming events in a distributed message broker environment.

### Key Learning Objectives

- Understanding Kafka broker architecture and connectivity
- Building Kafka producers that send event data
- Building Kafka consumers that receive and process event data
- Handling topic management and configuration
- Working with consumer groups and offset management
- JSON serialization/deserialization for event data
- Error handling and retry mechanisms
- Message flow in a distributed system


